@ScottPresler Florida schools dont do anything when i was in middle school I was in the gym locker room and some kid put a bag over my head and said kill the white boy,  we told the school and they said stop bullying

So my mom is here and alive today doing well and this is why I believe in miracles, my mom is a miracle and she is stronger then ever.  Stop spreading negativity! Life is too short for it and you never know when your day is. Keep your head up and show love everyday

And to hear that makes me really realize how short like really is,  dont hold grudges with the past/ anybody who you have drama with. Drop it and show some love spread positivity, god is really great and they saved my mom with the help of prayers and god.

She healed tremendously fast and she is now home doing better then ever, yes she is still in pain and yes she is having a hard time remembering somethings but the doctors said she is their miracle, she should not be alive right now.

They slowed down the bleeding and it didnt increase but she was still bleeding, she was in the icu for three to four days then they moved her to a regular room for four days with a tube in her stomach and a bag to collect the blood.

They rushed her back into surgery due to bleeding more they said she had something called dic and not many people live that have it.  They did two other surgerys on her with seven blood transfusions, she flatlined three times, they revived her

Hurt more and more and my stoned dad told the doctor and they examined her again and she had internal bleeding, with a ruptured uterus.   They did immediate surgery on her and they couldnt find the bleeding so they gave her a blood transfusion.

I wrapped my mom in a blanket and off she went to the hospital.  She sat in the ER for four hours and when they finally took her in they said its a bladder infection and they tried sending her home, while she is waiting for the discharge papers and she starts to

A few days go by and me and my step dad come home from McDonalds getting food, we come home to my mom in her room leaning on the bed crying in pain and freezing cold, my step dad didnt have the chance to eat he packed a little bag with everything he needed,

She was having an emergency C-Section due to the baby having very low blood sugar and my mom having very high blood pressure.  They got the baby out and her blood sugar was still low but they luckily got it up and she was a Healthy baby! She was born 1/23/18

It was a normal day I was sleeping and my mom had a doctors appointment to get a Ultrasound of her new baby girl, she was 32 weeks pregnant I believe.  So I wake up to some exciting yet terrifying, i was told my mom was having an emergency C-Section.
Life is too short for hate, take a moment to text your parents tell them you love them, you never know when your day is. Prayers for #parklandshooting #floridashooting #Florida
